reviews.review_text:
Nice Thanks for making this available. I just stumbled onto it tonight . . . "in the dark."

I like this period because they started to sound PROUD again. Like they all of a sudden realized "you know what, we're pretty good!" I like the care and attention they're giving the music. Nurturing it along. Listen to how Phil is singing "Box of Rain" for example. This is some fine music!

solid show from the "In The Dark" era Love 900,000 Tons of Steel by Brent M. they barely played that live but it was 1 of the best tunes on the album. Solid setlist...Liked the setlists better from 87-90 than the ones from 91-95
